# Portal EDL

Before editing portal templates or UI chrome, read and follow:

**[`docs/portal-experience-design-language.md`](docs/portal-experience-design-language.md)**

Enforce with:

```bash
uv run pytest tests/test_portal_edl.py -q
uv run python scripts/check_portal_edl.py
```

Key MUST rules: no status text/badges inside `<button>`; Dry Run → Apply on onboard-results; modals `role="dialog"` + Escape; `pr_url` via `safe_url`; badges ≥ 12px (`var(--font-xs)`); Events bell/drawer IA; CSS variables only for new chrome; list/log GET filters use compact `.filter-bar` (not oversized `.action-bar` selects).
